      <div xml:id="NA375-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu varaiyātu neṭuṅ kālam vantoḻukat talaimakaḷatu nilai uṇarnta tōḻi (ET: talaimakaṉai) varaivu kaṭāyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is how the confidante urged for marriage who perceived HER state when [HE] was coming for a long time without marrying.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA375">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            nīṭuciṉaip puṉṉai naṟuntā tutirak</l>
<l>            kōṭupuṉai kurukiṉ ṟōṭutalaip peyarum</l>
<l>            palpūṅ kāṉaṉ malkunīrc cērppa</l>
<l>            vaṉpilai yātaliṟ ṟaṉpula ṉayanta</l>
<l>            veṉṉu nāṇu naṉṉuta luvappa</l>
<l>            varuvai yāyiṉō naṉṟē peruṅkaṭa</l>
<l>            liravuttalai maṇṭilam peyarnteṉa vuravuttirai</l>
<l>            yeṟivaṉa pōla varūu</l>
<l>            muyarmaṇaṟ paṭappaiyem muṟaivi ṉūrē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l rend="indent2">          Since you have no love,</l>
<l>          o man from the coast of rising waters by the seashore grove of many flowers,</l>
<l rend="indent">            where the flocks of herons decorating the branches gather together,</l>
<l rend="indent3">            while fragrant pollen drops from the long-branched Puṉṉai tree,</l>
<l>          if you come [nevertheless?], so that [she with] good forehead rejoices,</l>
<l rend="indent">            who is ashamed even with me that longed for her opinion(?),</l>
<l rend="indent4">             it [will be] good,</l>
<l rend="indent">            – to the village of our residence in the garden with high sand,</l>
<l rend="indent2">            where the strong waves are coming as if they were dashing,</l>
<l rend="indent3">            because the [moon] disk is moving at night, in the great sea.</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
